CnhYOBLun1lzM0mKsacBToxw==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering project dependencies**\\n\\nI'm looking into Project JDK 21, noting that version 2.3.1 commonly supports Java 9 and up. I’m pondering if GraalVM Native Image includes certain dependencies. Perhaps `javax.xml.bind:jaxb-api:2.3.0` could be a test dependency? I’ll need to check Maven Central for that. It’s a lot to think about, but I want to ensure that I’m covering all necessary components for the project’s requirements.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_vBclGY17oBvgsqNRy1Bq16js|fc_04715431ba2212ec016a41266914808197a788ed87c51ae6e8", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "tmp=$(mktemp -d); cd \"$tmp\"; cat > pom.xml <<'EOF'\n<project xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\" xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 https://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\">\n<modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion><groupId>x</groupId><artifactId>x</artifactId><version>1</version>\n<dependencies>\n<dependency><groupId>com.sun.jersey</groupId><artifactId>jersey-grizzly2</artifactId><version>1.9</version></dependency>\n<dependency><groupId>javax.xml.bind</groupId><artifactId>jaxb-api</artifactId><version>2.3.1</version></dependency>\n</dependencies>\n</project>\nEOF\nmvn -q dependency:build-classpath -Dmdep.outputFile=cp.txt\ncat > TestJerseyGrizzly.java <<'EOF'\nimport com.sun.jersey.api.container.grizzly2.GrizzlyServerFactory; import com.sun.jersey.api.core.*; import javax.ws.rs.*; import javax.ws.rs.core.UriBuilder; import java.net.*; import org.glassfish.grizzly.http.server.HttpServer;\npublic class TestJerseyGrizzly { @Path(\"/hello\") public static class HelloResource { @GET public String hello(){return \"hello\";} } public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception { ResourceConfig config = new DefaultResourceConfig(HelloResource.class); HttpServer server = GrizzlyServerFactory.createHttpServer(UriBuild